The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Lanka eves 

 thrash Pak

 Asia Cup

 Jaipur: 

 Captain Shashikala Sriwardane led from the front as 

 Sri Lanka scored a thumping seven-wicket win over Pakistan 

 in the womens Asia Cup cricket tournament at the Sawai 

 Man Singh stadium here on Thursday.

 Shasikala invited Pakistan to 

 bat and took four wickets to restrict them to 147 for 9. 

 For Pakistan, opener Taskeena Qadeer (37) and Sana Mir (23) 

 were the only ones to defy the Lankan attack.

 The Sri Lankan captain then scored 

 44 and along with C. Polgampala (53) took her team to victory 

 in 43.2 overs with seven wickets to spare.

 Sri Lanka will take on India on 

 Thursday.

 BRIEF SCORES

 Pakistan 147/9 in 50 ovs 

 (Taskeena Qadeer 37; Shashikala Sriwardane 4/34). Sri 

 Lanka 151/3 in 43.2 ovs (Sriwardane 44, C. Polgampala 

 53). Sri Lanka won by 7 wkts.

 (PTI)




